August 24 - 28 , 1998 Location : University of Vienna , Austria The latest information about the workshop is available on WWW at : http : / / www . ifi . uni-klu . ac . at / ~ harald / pdb . html - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Workshop proceedings to be published by IEEE Computer Society Press - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Technical description Recent developments in parallel architectures ( e . g . piles of PCs , ATM-based machines , new RAID hardwares . . . ) and high performance networks ( e . g . ATM , fast Ethernet , system area networks . . . ) , combined with the emergence of new intensive data consuming applications ( e . g . multimedia , video , data mining , medical picture archiving systems , decision support . . . ) offer parallel databases a great opportunity to step from its traditional but limited "niche" of the very large databases and super computing to every day life applications . In this context , the aim of this workshop is to propose to scientists and industrial a forum to discuss these new trends in parallel architectures , high performance networks and high performance data storage facilities and their potential application to database applications and data management systems . Theoretical contributions are also encouraged if a potential link with applications is clearly stated . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Keywords Topics of interest include but are not limited to : Parallel query processing and optimization Data storage and management Task allocation and migration , query mapping Load balancing Parallelization on top of pile of PCs Parallel databases on Distributed Shared Memory Systems and Shared Disk Systems Parallel query languages Transaction Processing Performance evaluation and benchmarking Applications of interest include but are not limited to : Video on demand servers Multimedia Documentary databases Image servers Data mining Data warehouses Decision support systems Federated databases Cooperative applications - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Submission details All papers will be refereed by at least 2 members of the program committee .
